# GoWithMe Test Project

This is a Playwright E2E test suite for https://gowithme.app — a free platform connecting travelers with flight companions.

## Project Structure

- `src/pages/` — Page Object Models (POM). Every page gets its own class extending `BasePage`.
- `src/fixtures/` — Playwright custom fixtures that inject page objects into tests.
- `src/helpers/` — Shared utilities (constants, accessibility checks).
- `tests/` — Test specs organized by feature: `smoke/`, `navigation/`, `discover/`, `auth/`.
- `docs/TEST-PLAN.md` — Living documentation of all tests. Update this whenever tests are added or changed.

## Key Conventions

- Always use Page Object Model — never use raw selectors in test files.
- Use custom fixtures from `src/fixtures/test.fixture.ts` instead of bare `@playwright/test`.
- Prefer user-facing locators: `getByRole`, `getByText`, `getByLabel` over CSS/XPath.
- Tests must be independent and not rely on execution order.
- Every new test must be documented in `docs/TEST-PLAN.md`.
